description: This specification defines accelerometer sensor interface for obtaining information about acceleration applied to the X, Y and Z axis of a device that hosts the sensor.
title: Accelerometer

description: This specification defines a means to receive events that correspond to a light sensor detecting the presence of a light.
title: Ambient Light Sensor

description: This document captures common practices in designing APIs that fit well into the Web platform as a whole, using WebIDL.
title: Web API Design Cookbook

description: This document describes privacy best practices for web applications, including those that might use device APIs.
title: Web Application Privacy Best Practices

description: This specification defines a new DOM event type that provides information about the battery status of the hosting device and associated auxiliary devices.
title: Battery Status API

description: The Compute Pressure API provides a way for websites to react to changes in the CPU pressure of the target device, such that websites can trade off resources for an improved user experience.
title: Compute Pressure Level 1

description: An API to give one-off access to a user’s contact information with full control over the shared data.
title: Contact Picker API

description: These are the requirements intended to be met in the development of client-side APIs that enable the creation of Web Applications and Web Widgets that interact with devices services such as Calendar, Contacts, Camera, etc.
title: Device APIs Requirements

description: This document defines requirements for controlling access to device APIs, illustrated by corresponding use cases.
title: Device API Access Control Use Cases and Requirements

description: This document provides definitions, use cases, and requirements for making device APIs more privacy-friendly.
title: Device API Privacy Requirements

description: This document specifies an API that allows web applications to request and be notified of changes of the posture of a foldable device.
title: Device Posture API

description: The Generic Sensor API defines a framework and abstract Sensor interface to provide a consistent basis for writing for concrete sensor specifications. It is intended to be extended to accommodate different sensor types.
title: Generic Sensor API

description: This specification defines the GeolocationSensor interface for obtaining geolocation of the hosting device.
title: Geolocation Sensor

description: This specification defines a concrete sensor interface to monitor the rate of rotation around the device’s local three primary axes.
title: Gyroscope

description: This document lists the design goals and requirements that potential W3C recommendations should support in order to enable access to services and content provided by home network devices on other devices, including the discovery and playback of content available to those devices, both from services such as traditional broadcast media and internet based services but also from the home network.
title: Requirements for Home Networking Scenarios

description: This specification defines a concrete sensor interface to measure magnetic field in the X, Y and Z axis.
title: Magnetometer

description: The Motion Sensors Explainer Note is an introduction to low-level and high-level motion sensors, their relationship, inner workings and common use-cases.
title: Motion Sensors Explainer

description: This specification defines several new DOM event types that provide information about the physical orientation and motion of a hosting device.
title: DeviceOrientation Event Specification

description: This specification defines a base orientation sensor interface and concrete sensor subclasses to monitor the device’s physical orientation in relation to a stationary three dimensional Cartesian coordinate system.
title: Orientation Sensor

description: This specification defines a means to receive events that correspond to a proximity sensor detecting the presence of a physical object.
title: Proximity Sensor

description: This document specifies an API that allows web applications to request a screen wake lock. Under the right conditions, and if allowed, the screen wake lock prevents the system from turning off a device's screen.
title: Screen Wake Lock API
